data.content:
**In .NET 11, all your sync calls will throw at runtime — the sync-over-async opt-in is gone.**

EF Core 11 **fully removed** synchronous I/O for the Cosmos DB provider. In EF Core 10 you could opt in to sync-over-async; in EF Core 11 that opt-in no longer exists. Calling `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, or `SaveChanges()` against the Cosmos provider **always throws**.

### What to fix

Convert every method to its async equivalent:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

You'll also need to update every caller to `await` these methods and propagate `async`/`Task` up the call chain. There is no workaround — sync I/O on the Cosmos provider is permanently removed.

**Tracking issue:** https://github.com/dotnet/efcore/issues/37059
